            "answer_text": "By album: Kill 'em All: None Ride the Lightning: Fade to Black (speeds up towards end) Master of Puppets: Welcome Home (Sanitarium) -- also speeds up towards end And Justice for All: One (only beginning, then gets real heavy), To Live is to Die (Heavy, but slow instrumental) Black Album: Nothing Else Matters, Unforgiven Load: Hero of the Day (sort of but more upbeat), Mama Says Reload: Low Man's Lyrics, Unforgiven II Garage, Inc. (cover tunes): Turn the Page, Tuesday's Gone, Loverman (kind of, but not like the others) St. Anger: None really; the closest you get to slow on that album is The Unnamed Feeling Death Magnetic: The Day that Never Comes (speeds up in second half), Unforgiven III ",
